                        transfers ownership.

                    - CATEGORY: (SPECIFICATION|INFORMATIONAL|EXPERIMENTAL)

                        - Specification means this document is standard.
                        - Informational means this is a supporting document.
                        - Experimental means this document is in prototype stage.

                    - STATUS: (DRAFT|REVIEW|STABLE|DEPRECATED|OBSOLETE)

                        - Draft means this document in a work in progress.
                        - Review means this document is being audited.
                        - Stable means this document is in production.
                        - Deprecated means this document will soon be obsolete.
                        - Obsolete means this document was deprecated and
                        unsupported.

